## every script in this dir is a git hook.

## PREREQUISITES:
##    Windows: Git for Windows must be installed (https://gitforwindows.org/) The Git-bash app makes all of this magic happen.
## Linux, Mac: Git must be installed
##        All: Bash version > 4.0 (if lint.sh is called)
##
## INSTALLATION:
## Run addGitHooks.sh in b2v-project
##
## MANUAL INSTALLATION:
## Symlink every script to .git/hooks
##     Windows:   mklink .git\hooks\$hook ..\..\tooling\hooks\$hook
##     Linux, Mac:   ln -s ../../tooling/hooks/$hook .git/hooks/$hook
##
## TO BYPASS:
##     git commit --no-verify
##
## References:
## https://codeinthehole.com/tips/tips-for-using-a-git-pre-commit-hook/
## https://www.viget.com/articles/two-ways-to-share-git-hooks-with-your-team/
## https://jondowdle.com/2015/02/block-merge-conflicts-in-commits/
## https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/git-hooks
